ateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift`: high-value wake journey automation + telemetry IDs.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:98:- `scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`: CI entrypoint that runs exploratory wake UI test and writes report.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:99:- `README.md`: current app IA/value framing baseline.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:180:- `scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`: prove telemetry report still captures visited screens and tapped IDs after identifier updates.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:181:- Add screenshot-manifest validation test (new, repo-local): prove required before/after screenshot IDs and variants exist in manifest JSON.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:184:- Current baseline artifact status: real baseline capture is currently blocked in this worker because `xcrun` is unavailable; baseline manifest should be captured in hosted iOS validation environment.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:185:- Required before/after states per screen (`onboarding`, `home`, `primary_list`, `create_edit`, `active_task`, `completion`, `history_streaks`, `profile_settings`, `paywall_subscription`):\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:186:  - `before/default`\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:187:  - `after/default`\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:219:  - Keep existing IDs as aliases for one release where feasible, then migrate tests to new IDs and remove aliases after CI/Appium parity passes.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:220:  - Avoid renaming dynamic prefix IDs (`wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeMissionButton-*`) to keep exploratory selectors stable.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:236:  - Exit tests: updated unit/UI/paywall tests pass; Appium exploratory test passes with migrated IDs.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:238:  - Scope: hosted iOS screenshot capture, contrast/VoiceOver/Dynamic Type/reduced-motion checks, and regression triage.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:239:  - Deliverables: before/after screenshot manifest, UX validation notes, and postmortem learning capture artifact.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:240:  - Exit tests: screenshot-manifest gate + accessibility checklist + acceptance criteria signoff.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:248:- UITest/Appium selectors remain discoverable and CI-stable after identifier migration.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:249:- Hosted iOS validation produces required before/after screenshot states, including Dynamic Type and dark mode.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md:265:- Current worker lacks simulator tooling (`xcrun`), so visual verification must run in hosted iOS environment.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:35:      \"primary_action\": \"Advance setup with Continue/Finish setup after each explicit selection.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:54:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:86:        \"Focus order prioritizes commitment content before analytics tiles.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:91:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:96:        \"Dark and light mode screenshots remain readable.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:128:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:165:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:195:        \"VoiceOver announces state banner before interactive controls.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:201:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:233:        \"Focus order prioritizes next-best action before tertiary links.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:238:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:275:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:312:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:330:      \"primary_action\": \"Start trial or upgrade after clear value explanation and plan context.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:349:      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json:359:  \"no_clone_statement\": \"The screen specs adapt abstract patterns only and do not copy another app's assets, copy, brand, visual composition, screenshots, or proprietary interaction sequences.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:4:- Product emotion: grounded first impression, low-friction wake execution, steady recovery after misses.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:24:- Focus order: top-down, action-first in wake-critical screens, with fallback action immediately after primary CTA.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:59:  - Light/dark screenshots preserve readable hierarchy and non-color state cues.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:80:  - Focus order prioritizes commitment card and primary CTA before analytics tiles.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:89:  - Light/dark mode screenshots preserve legibility and hierarchy.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:145:  - Error screenshot shows preserved input and clear correction guidance.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:165:  - VoiceOver announces current state before actionable controls.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:174:  - Dark/light screenshots both show clear CTA contrast.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:195:  - Focus order prioritizes next action before tertiary links.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:271:- Primary action: start subscription only after clear value comparison.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:296:- Core status remains understandable in both light and dark mode screenshots.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md:303:These specs adapt abstract UX patterns only and do not copy another app’s assets, copy, brand, visual composition, screenshots, or proprietary interaction sequences.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.json:33:        \"paywall_subscription\": \"Surface premium contextually after value moments and never interrupt active wake execution.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.json:61:        \"primary_list\": \"Sort by urgency before recency and display state tokens in each row.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.json:67:        \"paywall_subscription\": \"Show premium after proof moments and avoid interrupting active wake flow.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.json:117:      \"paywall_subscription\": \"Trigger contextual premium prompts after value moments and never in urgent wake execution.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.json:120:  \"no_clone_statement\": \"The winning UX adapts abstract patterns only and does not copy another app's assets, copy, branding, visual composition, screenshots, or proprietary interaction sequences.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.md:36:`calm_accountability_direction` wins after adversarial critique because it best satisfies the required blend of iOS-native quality, half-awake clarity, accessibility guardrails, and feasible execution while still being commercially viable without coercive conversion tactics. It is differentiated through tone and recovery architecture rather than novelty-for-novelty visuals, and it leaves room for selective motivational overlays outside urgent wake moments.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.md:51:- paywall_subscription: position premium as reliability tools and deeper insights after value moments; never block active wake execution.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.md:56:- Conversion rules: contextual upsell only after demonstrated value; no fake scarcity, forced countdowns, or obstructive close behavior.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.md:61:- Contrast: token-level audits in light/dark/high-contrast modes before release.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.md:69:- Missing simulator tooling previously blocked baseline visual capture; hosted iOS validation remains required before UX sign-off.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/tournament-consensus.md:72:The selected UX adapts abstract interaction patterns only and does not copy any external app assets, copywriting, branding, visual composition, screenshots, or proprietary interaction choreography.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/cross-critique.md:12:- `gamified_streak_direction`: Good momentum framing and clear “today mission” hierarchy. Risk: streak context and progress ring add interpretation overhead; tired users may parse “game state” before core action.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/cross-critique.md:37:- `gamified_streak_direction`: Highest risk; custom timeline/rings plus multi-state gamification logic increase SwiftUI state complexity, animation/haptics coordination burden, and screenshot test matrix size.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/cross-critique.md:71:- Role-specific recommendation: Accessibility critic requires hard acceptance criteria before approving `hard_wake_direction` or `gamified_streak_direction` (AX text expansion, contrast, VoiceOver semantics on status artifacts).\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/cross-critique.md:72:- Integration suggestion for tournament scoring: treat `calm_accountability_direction` as baseline architecture, then A/B limited motivational overlays from `gamified_streak_direction` outside urgent wake flow.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/minimal_native_direction.md:33:Primary risks are tiny controls, color-only urgency, alarm stress, haptics-only feedback, and cognitive overload after waking. Mitigate with VoiceOver labels, Dynamic Type layouts, clear focus order, high contrast, reduced motion, large hit targets, and alternate task types for different abilities.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/minimal_native_direction.md:36:This direction has low SwiftUI risk because it uses native components and semantic tokens. Risks are mostly in making active-task states visually distinct without custom complexity and ensuring screenshots/Appium flows can verify all states. It avoids broad boilerplate rewrites.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/minimal_native_direction.md:49:Do not copy competitor layouts, Mobbin screenshots, PageFlows screen compositions, brand systems, exact copy, icons, animations, alarm sounds, or proprietary challenge sequences.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/gamified_streak_direction.md:36:- Minimum readable sizes: 17pt body baseline; captions never below 12pt at default and must scale upward.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/gamified_streak_direction.md:82:- Scope tradeoffs: prioritize wake-state clarity and history reason-codes before advanced reward cosmetics.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/hard_wake_direction.md:3:- First 10 seconds: immediate urgency with control, like a safety checklist before takeoff.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/hard_wake_direction.md:42:- Minimum readable sizes: 17pt body baseline, 15pt secondary metadata, never below 13pt for tappable-context labels.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/hard_wake_direction.md:60:- Paywall/subscription: shown after value proof moments (post-completion/history insight), never interrupting an active wake flow.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/hard_wake_direction.md:82:- Scope tradeoffs: if time-constrained, prioritize active-task clarity and history explanations before visual polish.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/hard_wake_direction.md:104:- Any proprietary screenshots, icon packs, brand palettes, or marketing copy.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/calm_accountability_direction.md:52:- History/streaks: show reliability trend + \"why changed\" annotations; include one-tap repair planning after misses.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/calm_accountability_direction.md:54:- Paywall/subscription: premium framed as reliability tools and deeper insights, surfaced contextually after value moments, never blocking urgent wake flows.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/directions/calm_accountability_direction.md:92:- Recovery-first accountability language after misses.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/codex/screen-flows.prompt.md:15:- current app source, tests, Appium identifiers, screenshot manifest, and previews\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/codex/screen-flows.prompt.md:43:- update tests, previews, screenshot manifests, or Appium flows needed to prove the redesigned states\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/codex/screen-flows.prompt.md:52:- Treat competitor and Mobbin/Pageflows references as abstract pattern evidence only. Do not copy assets, copy, screenshots, brand identity, layouts, or proprietary interaction sequences.\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/codex/screen-flows.prompt.md:82:- screenshot evidence is ready for UX review and includes before/after states where available\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/codex/visual-system.json:10:  \"stdout_excerpt\": \"Implemented the visual-system scope in DesignSystem and wrote the required evidence file.\\n\\nChanged files:\\n- [WakeVisualTokens.swift](/home/daytona/workspace/apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/WakeVisualTokens.swift)\\n- [WakeVisualComponents.swift](/home/daytona/workspace/apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/WakeVisualComponents.swift)\\n- [WakeVisualSystemTests.swift](/home/daytona/workspace/apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Tests/DesignSystemTests/WakeVisualSystemTests.swift)\\n- [visual-system.md](/home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/evidence/visual-system.md)\\n\\nWhat was implemented:\\n- Expanded wake semantic tokens for state coverage: disabled, destructive, success, warning, premium, active task, focus/high-contrast, divider/material/shadow semantics.\\n- Added typography helper behavior for multiline-safe Dynamic Type usage and applied it across wake components.\\n- Refined reusable wake components (cards, rows, status/progress, primary/secondary actions, empty/loading/error, premium callout, completion feedback) with stronger accessibility and focus-order support.\\n- Added/updated previews to cover key states including dark mode, Dynamic Type, and increased contrast.\\n- Extended token/component test assertions for new wake visual semantics.\\n\\nVerification status:\\n- `swift test` could not run in this worker because `swift` is not installed (`swift: command not found`).\\n- Evidence document includes command log, acceptance-criteria mapping, component inventory, accessibility notes, screenshot states, risks, and pending verifier note exactly as requested.\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/codex/visual-system.last-message.md:18:- Evidence document includes command log, acceptance-criteria mapping, component inventory, accessibility notes